#  Our instance namespace:
@prefix dd: <http://moschetti.org/buzz#> .

#  The foundation AMI namespace:
@prefix ami: <http://moschetti.org/ami#> .

#  Industry standards:
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .


dd:xx7ey4sh  a	ami:Control ;
	     rdfs:label "simple" ;
	     rdfs:comment """
This is a simple domain of data.  It shows how people ("Actors"), software,
and hardware come together in AMI.  This domain has a single system that
has a single program: the venerable Hello World.  Although Hello World does
not highlight many more exciting capavilities of AMI, it helps a newcomer
understand the important relationship between software, components, and
runtimes which is a key design feature of AMI.  Hello World has no inputs
and no practical outputs and therefore there is also no declaration of Shapes
in the system, another important AMI class -- but we will tackle these
concepts in a different domain.
""" .


#  Set up 2 Actors
dd:ac1bf4e4 a ami:Actor;
    rdfs:label "Steve Austin" ;
    ami:salary   "10.09"^^xsd:decimal ;	
    ami:DID "A123" ;
    ami:firstname "Steve" ;
    ami:lastname "Austin" .
    
dd:ac78a6qz a ami:Actor;
    rdfs:label "Dave Spector" ;
    ami:DID "A456" ;
    ami:firstname "Dave" ;
    ami:lastname "Spector" .


dd:vn6et9uh	    a ami:Vendor ;
		    ami:owner dd:ac1bf4e4 ;
		    ami:steward dd:ac78a6qz ;
		    ami:LEI "C003" ;
		    rdfs:label "My Company Inc." ;
		    rdfs:comment """
My Company Inc. specializes in extremely simple software.  They are the prime
vendor of Hello World.
""" .


dd:sw0r5i28   a ami:Software ;
	      ami:owner dd:ac1bf4e4 ;
	      ami:steward dd:ac78a6qz ;
	      ami:vendor dd:vn6et9uh ;
	      ami:version [ a ami:Version; ami:major 8; ami:minor 2; ami:patch 3;
      		  ami:released "2006-01-01T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
                  ami:bintype "x86_64"; ami:platform "ubuntu" ];
	      ami:slang "c" ;
	      ami:EOL "2024-12-10T12:00:00.000Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
	      rdfs:label "hello world";
	      rdfs:comment """
The time-honored "hello world" program, in the original C language.
""" .
	      


